doc.after: Five A380s were built for testing and demonstration purposes.[35] The first A380, registered F-WWOW, was unveiled in Toulouse 18 January 2005.[36] Its first flight took place at 10:29Â am local time (08:29 UTC) on 27 April 2005.[37] This plane, equipped with Rolls-Royce Trent 900 engines, flew from Toulouse Blagnac International Airport with a crew of six headed by chief test pilot Jacques Rosay.[38] After landing, 3 hours 54 minutes later, Rosay said flying the A380 had been "like handling a bicycle".[39]
